Blaze at Rajabazar house, 60 rescued.
KOLKATA: A fire on the first floor of a two-storey building on Raja Dinendra Street, Rajabazar, around 4.25pm on Sunday triggered panic among residents of the area.
The incident scared the people more as a wedding ceremony was being held nearby. Soon, the fire spread to an adjacent building. The fire department had to deploy 10 fire engines to control the blaze. Around 60 people were rescued from the building, where the fire broke out.
The firemen are yet to find out the cause of the blaze, but they suspect it was due to a short circuit. Police said no one was injured. Residents of the area rushed to the spot to help with the rescue operation and managed to evacuate all the occupants.
